        "content": "## How to trace a specific request\n\nEvery API response includes an **`X-Trace-ID`** header (UUID format). This ID links the response to logs and the database.\n\n**Step 1 — From the response header:**\n```\nX-Trace-ID: 758c97c4-a468-4cf5-9c98-5xxxxxxx\n```\n\n**Step 2 — Look up in usage logs:**\n```bash\ncurl http://localhost:8000/api/v1/admin/usage/logs \\\n  -H \"X-API-Key: ms_admin_default_key_change_me\"\n```\nReturns: tokens used, latency_ms, status_code, model, timestamp.\n\n**Step 3 — Search container logs:**\n```bash\ndocker logs maintserve-api-1 2>&1 | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nfor line in sys.stdin:\n    try:\n        d = json.loads(line)\n        if d.get('trace_id') == '<YOUR-TRACE-ID>':\n            print(line.rstrip())\n    except: pass\n\"\n```",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "How to Trace a Request (X-Trace-ID)",
      "type": "text"
    }

